_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                   1XTC 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details           
;CHOLERA TOXIN CONTAINS 3 KINDS OF CHAINS: AN ALPHA
AND A GAMMA CHAIN (FROM THE SAME PRECURSOR MOLECULE),
LINKED BY AN INTERCHAIN DISULFIDE BOND, ASSOCIATED
NONCOVALENTLY WITH AN AGGREGATE OF 4 TO 6 BETA CHAINS.
CHAIN A IS THE A1 OR ALPHA CHAIN, CHAIN C IS THE A2 OR
GAMMA CHAIN, AND CHAINS D, E, F, G, AND H ARE THE FIVE
ASSOCIATED BETA CHAINS.
;
